.TH "create_bbt" 9 "create_bbt" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
create_bbt \- [GENERIC] Create a bad block table by scanning the device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" create_bbt
.BI "(struct nand_chip *this "  ","
.BI "uint8_t *buf "  ","
.BI "struct nand_bbt_descr *bd "  ","
.BI "int chip "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "this" 12
NAND chip object
.IP "buf" 12
temporary buffer
.IP "bd" 12
descriptor for the good/bad block search pattern
.IP "chip" 12
create the table for a specific chip, -1 read all chips; applies only
if NAND_BBT_PERCHIP option is set
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Create a bad block table by scanning the device for the given good/bad block
identify pattern.
